snippet: The tests broke the recent relative silence from the North, but the move was much less provocative than what had been feared earlier this year.
abstract: South Korean officials say North Korea launched three short-range missiles into sea off its east coast; tests break relative silence from the North, but move is much less provocative than what had been feared in tense weeks after country's nuclear test in February 2013

byline.contributor: Mark Mazzetti contributed reporting from Washington.

lead_paragraph: The tests broke the recent relative silence from the North, but the move was much less provocative than what had been feared earlier this year.

headline.seo: South Korea Says North Launches 3 Missiles Into Sea
headline.main: North Korea Reportedly Launches Short-Range Missiles
headline.print_headline: North Korea Reportedly Launches Short-Range Missiles
